      • displayGuiScreen

        public void displayGuiScreen(@Nullable
                             Screen guiScreenIn)
        Sets the argument GuiScreen as the main (topmost visible) screen.

        WARNING: This method is not thread-safe. Opening GUIs from a thread other than the main thread may cause many different issues, including the GUI being rendered before it has initialized (leading to unusual crashes). If on a thread other than the main thread, use #addScheduledTask: 

         minecraft.addScheduledTask(() -> minecraft.displayGuiScreen(gui));
